{
    "id": 23261,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - December 03, 2013",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 288.504,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 288.504,
                "byte_start": 106496,
                "byte_stop": 0,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 7.49,
                        "byte_start": 106496,
                        "byte_stop": 136485,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.49,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 136485,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has our opinion this morning in case 12-562, United States versus Woods."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.49,
                        "stop": 288.504,
                        "byte_start": 136485,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.49,
                                "stop": 13.658,
                                "byte_start": 136485,
                                "byte_stop": 161144,
                                "text": "This is case here on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.658,
                                "stop": 22.075,
                                "byte_start": 161144,
                                "byte_stop": 194894,
                                "text": "The case involves a type of tax shelter that was marketed to high income taxpayers in the late 1990s."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.075,
                                "stop": 38.626,
                                "byte_start": 194894,
                                "byte_stop": 261036,
                                "text": "The mechanics of the shelter were complex, but its aim was simple, to artificially inflate a taxpayer\u0027s basis in a partnership so that the taxpayer could claim huge losses when the partnership\u0027s assets were disposed of."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.626,
                                "stop": 56.119,
                                "byte_start": 261036,
                                "byte_stop": 331045,
                                "text": "In this case, respondent Gary Woods and his employer, Billy Joe McCombs contributed roughly $3.2 million in cash and financial instruments to two partnerships which used the cash to purchase stock and currency."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.119,
                                "stop": 70.95,
                                "byte_start": 331045,
                                "byte_stop": 390395,
                                "text": "When those assets were later sold for modest gains, Woods and McCombs claimed that their extremely high tax basis in the two partnerships gave them losses of more than $45 million."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.95,
                                "stop": 78.897,
                                "byte_start": 390395,
                                "byte_stop": 422160,
                                "text": "How the tax shelter produced that high tax basis is too tedious to recite. [Laughter]"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.897,
                                "stop": 106.815,
                                "byte_start": 422160,
                                "byte_stop": 533859,
                                "text": "The IRS ruled that the partnerships had no genuine business purpose, but were shams that could be disregarded for tax purposes.As a result, the IRS concluded that to the extent Woods and McCombs underpaid their taxes by claiming a basis in the partnerships greater than zero, they would be subject to the statutory 40% penalty for gross valuation misstatements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.815,
                                "stop": 110.298,
                                "byte_start": 533859,
                                "byte_stop": 547756,
                                "text": "Woods sought judicial review on behalf of the partnerships."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.298,
                                "stop": 120.046,
                                "byte_start": 547756,
                                "byte_stop": 586731,
                                "text": "The District Court held that the partnerships were properly disregarded as shams, but that the valuation misstatement penalty did not apply."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.046,
                                "stop": 121.841,
                                "byte_start": 586731,
                                "byte_stop": 593941,
                                "text": "The Fifth Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.841,
                                "stop": 129.574,
                                "byte_start": 593941,
                                "byte_stop": 624870,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to consider the applicability of the penalty and we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.574,
                                "stop": 138.194,
                                "byte_start": 624870,
                                "byte_stop": 659352,
                                "text": "At the onset, we hold the District Court had jurisdiction to consider the valuation misstatement penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.194,
                                "stop": 145.299,
                                "byte_start": 659352,
                                "byte_stop": 687773,
                                "text": "Congress has enacted a two-stage structure for adjudicating tax matters related to partnerships."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.299,
                                "stop": 156.896,
                                "byte_start": 687773,
                                "byte_stop": 734166,
                                "text": "Partnerships themselves are not taxed, it\u0027s only the partners who are taxed when the partnership distributes money or property to them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.896,
                                "stop": 169.875,
                                "byte_start": 734166,
                                "byte_stop": 786098,
                                "text": "In the first stage, items applicable to the partnership as a whole and penalties related to those items are determined in unified proceedings at the partnership level."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.875,
                                "stop": 179.119,
                                "byte_start": 786098,
                                "byte_stop": 822983,
                                "text": "In the second stage, those partnership level determinations are used to adjust the tax liability of the individual partners."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.119,
                                "stop": 182.64,
                                "byte_start": 822983,
                                "byte_stop": 837089,
                                "text": "This case involves a proceeding at the partnership level."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.64,
                                "stop": 188.723,
                                "byte_start": 837089,
                                "byte_stop": 861435,
                                "text": "No one disputes that the District Court had jurisdiction to determine that the partnerships were shams."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.723,
                                "stop": 210.892,
                                "byte_start": 861435,
                                "byte_stop": 950147,
                                "text": "Accordingly, the District Court also had jurisdiction to provisionally determine the applicability of any penalty that could result from the ruling that the partnerships were shams regardless of whether imposing the penalty would require additional determinations at the individual partner level which it always does."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.892,
                                "stop": 216.735,
                                "byte_start": 950147,
                                "byte_stop": 973448,
                                "text": "Turning to the merits, we hold that the valuation misstatement penalty is applicable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 216.735,
                                "stop": 237.969,
                                "byte_start": 973448,
                                "byte_stop": 1058398,
                                "text": "The penalty applies to the portion of any tax underpayment that is attributable to a substantial or gross valuation misstatement which exists where the value or the adjusted basis of any property claimed on a tax return exceeds the correct amount of that value or adjusted basis by a specified percentage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.969,
                                "stop": 241.625,
                                "byte_start": 1058398,
                                "byte_stop": 1073027,
                                "text": "The penalty\u0027s plain language makes it applicable here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 241.625,
                                "stop": 251.972,
                                "byte_start": 1073027,
                                "byte_stop": 1114405,
                                "text": "Once the partnerships were deemed not to exist for tax purposes, no partner could legitimately claim a basis in the partnerships greater than zero."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 251.972,
                                "stop": 266.381,
                                "byte_start": 1114405,
                                "byte_stop": 1172083,
                                "text": "Any underpayment resulting from the use of a non-zero outside basis would therefore be attributable to the taxpayer\u0027s having claimed an adjusted basis that exceeded the correct amount of that adjusted basis."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 266.381,
                                "stop": 282.363,
                                "byte_start": 1172083,
                                "byte_stop": 1236031,
                                "text": "And under the relevant treasury regulation which is not challenged here, when an asset\u0027s true adjusted basis is zero, the valuation misstatement is automatically deemed gross and is therefore subject to a 40% penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 282.363,
                                "stop": 285.834,
                                "byte_start": 1236031,
                                "byte_stop": 1249928,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Court of the Appeals for the Fifth Circuit is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 285.834,
                                "stop": 288.504,
                                "byte_start": 1249928,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court\u0027s decision is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
